To help ensure that the process controls and/or process hazards do not eventually deviate significantly from the original design safety features, the PHA team periodically updates and revalidates the hazard analysis results.  These periodic reviews are conducted at least every 5 years and will be conducted at this frequency until the process is no longer operating.  

The recommended order of analysis will be based upon the following criteria: 

A¿A· age of process; 
A¿A· extent of process hazards; 
A¿A· number of affected employees; and 
A¿A· operating history of the process.  

The results and findings from these updates are documented and retained.  The team findings are forwarded to management for consideration, and the final resolution of the findings is documented and retained.

